  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nSince #1429, you can write `console.log(\"Address %s is OK.\",myAddress)`. It would be helpful to have general access to the underlying format function.\r\n\r\nThis may be overkill, or may be an issue for `forge-std`, but I am guessing it would run faster to directly call the underlying format than to reimplement `%s`-substitution in Solidity.\r\n\r\nThen instead of\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nvm.writeLine(string.concat('\"',vm.toString(addr),'\": ',vm.toString(t.balanceOf(addr))));\r\n```\r\n\r\nyou can write\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nvm.writeLine('\"%s\": %s', addr, t.balanceOf(addr));\r\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
